                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15837561" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 25 Jan 2017 10:50:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I believe, in OSGI, the formatted services list handler did not see an initialized bus until CXF 3.1.8 but I see the check for the private endpoints can still fail now as the attempt to initialize a bus is done later.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16243971" author="anton-johansson" created="Wed, 8 Nov 2017 13:55:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I also want to get rid of the ?_wadl resources. However, this property does not bite. I&apos;ve tried 3.1.9 and 3.1.14 (which is stated to be fixed, according to this issue). Is there something else that I&apos;m missing, or is there another way of disabling the ?_wadl parameter?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16244135" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 8 Nov 2017 15:23:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you please debug and check the bus instance available in JAXRSServerFactoryBean (super class) and the one in ServiceListGeneratorServlet constructor and see if they are the same bus ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16244147" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 8 Nov 2017 15:27:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well this is only about hiding a link to the endpoint from the servlet services page.&lt;br/&gt;
If you&apos;d like to make sure that a wadl query returns 404 then set WADLGenerator#ignoreRequests to true&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16257204" author="anton-johansson" created="Fri, 17 Nov 2017 16:49:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ahh, okay, I understand. That did the trick, indeed, thanks a bunch for the quick response! And sorry for hijacking the wrong issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
